The United Democratic Alliance (UDA) has picked Bishop Margaret Wanjiru to fly the party's ticket in the Nairobi gubernatorial by-election.
The newly unveiled party associated with allies of the Deputy President William Ruto made the announcement on Friday in Nairobi. 
"We do not fear competition. We have a candidate here in Margaret Wanjiru. We win or we lose, that is a part of democracy," Elgeyo-Marakwet Senator Kipchumba Murkomen said.



